shortdesc.ph: Reports the result of uploading the SDK log files.

section.p: After calling, the SDK will trigger the callback to report the result of the log file upload. If the upload fails, refer to the `reason` parameter to troubleshoot.

plentry.pd: The request ID. The request ID is consistent with the requestId returned in. You can associate specific uploads with callbacks through requestId.

pd.p:
Whether the log file was uploaded successfully:
true: Successfully upload the log files.
false: Fails to upload the log files. For details, see the `reason` parameter.

plentry.pd: The reason for the upload failure. See .
